It is not the sprinkler line, it's the 5-6 inch galvanized main water line. We've gotten the water shut off and drained and the system is on test. 2nd riser is shut off, main drains are open and pumps are are per fire dept that showed up. Both the firefighters and myself could see the lines look rusted through on the two spots that burst.

The water flow has increased dramatically over the past 2 weeks. 
The area where the run off from the water leak is an area of high customer traffic. Since this area remains wet/damp the danger of a customer slip/fall is a constant safety concern.
